Explanation:

We use a simple loop to iterate from 1 to n. In each iteration, we multiply the result by 5 and take the modulo with 1000000007 to ensure the result is within the range of 1 to 10^9 + 7. Since the loop runs only once for each value of n, the time complexity is O(1), and the space complexity is also O(1) as we only use a single variable for the result.

